{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: diff extraction -> review-input builder. A unit test of only a parser can miss leakage when another module re-expands to full file. Integration brake: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no dependence on model output; no multi-agentic chain. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because behavior text is about scoping logic, not real HTTP/subprocess behavior.","test_description":"Run the real diff-ingestion and prompt/input-construction modules together using a fixture PR diff where unchanged lines contain obvious defects. Assert produced review input includes only changed hunks/line ranges and excludes unchanged content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on GitHub diff-position semantics and real API behavior; mocks can hide off-by-one/side-of-diff mapping failures. REAL-INFRA and MOCK-HIDE both push to System.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using known file/line anchors through the automation path, then fetch review comments from GitHub and verify each landed on the intended diff location (path + side + line/position) as rendered in PR diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pass/fail depends on real model judgment quality (finding a true defect), which deterministic stubs cannot validate (deterministic-assertion trap). Rejection gate: Workflow is disqualified because behavior asks for a single outcome (detect >=1 defect), not correctness of multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Use a real PR containing a seeded known bug and run the live analysis model on changed lines. Assert at least one returned finding correctly references the seeded defect location/type (with a stability criterion such as pass-rate over repeated runs).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module state integrity (inline-post results -> summary assembler). Integration catches mismatched IDs/run contamination. Integration brake: no real OS/network is required to expose mapping bugs; no model-output quality dependency; no multi-agentic chain. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because behavior text targets same-run ID linkage logic, not external API edge behavior.","test_description":"Execute pipeline modules with a controlled set of posted-inline-comment results (including run_id and comment IDs), build summary payload, and assert each summary finding references an existing inline comment ID from that run and no foreign/stale IDs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Loss can occur during handoff/aggregation across modules (collector, deduper, serializer), not just in one pure function. Integration brake: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no dependence on real model judgment; no multi-agentic sequence required.","test_description":"Feed multiple inline findings through the real aggregation + summary-payload construction path (including edge cases like duplicates and ordering), then assert payload cardinality and IDs preserve all expected inline findings with no omissions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires real PR execution over real HTTP/API calls and sequencing; in-process fakes can miss auth, rate-limit, payload-contract, and ordering failures. Rejection gate: Agentic is disqualified because findings are fixed/precomputed, so correctness does not depend on model output.","test_description":"Run end-to-end automation against a real test PR using a fixed findings fixture (no live model). Assert all stages succeed: diff fetched, inline comments created, summary posted, and posted artifacts match fixture counts/content references.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is full agent pipeline behavior with real model generation plus downstream posting and summarization; correctness depends on sequential agentic-to-non-agentic handoffs. MULTI-STEP and LLM-DEP together require Workflow. Lower levels miss pipeline-level failures like valid model findings failing later-stage linkage/posting under autonomous flow.","test_description":"Execute the live end-to-end run on a real PR using real model analysis and real GitHub posting. Assert autonomous completion with no manual fixes, with consistent artifacts across stages (generated findings -> inline comments -> summary linkage).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.28,"Workflow":0.62}}]}
